</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[179,1380,2622,2655]" pageId="112" pageNumber="390" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="112.[178,1383,1956,2852]" box="[179,1380,2622,2655]" pageId="112" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,311,2622,2655]" pageId="112" pageNumber="390">Breeding.</emphasis>
Pregnant Sinaloan Deermice were caught in April, with 1-3 embryos/female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[178,1137,2661,2694]" pageId="112" pageNumber="390" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="112.[178,1383,1956,2852]" box="[178,1137,2661,2694]" pageId="112" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[178,413,2661,2694]" pageId="112" pageNumber="390">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Sinaloan Deermouse is presumably nocturnal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
